		<description>Caliber: .303 British. 10-round detachable mag. Semi-Automatic.
		
An early Cold War bullpup self-loading rifle developed by Major Eric Hall of the United Kingdom. Feeding from a Lee-Enfield magazine, the EM-3 had an odd cartridge ejection system that was meant to send spent casings over the shooter's shoulder. Only drawings and a non-functional mockup of the real thing were ever produced, as the weapon seemed to attract little interest compared to the select-fire capable Thorpe EM-1 and Janson EM-2.</description>
